equipments.name: Circuit Breaker
equipments.description: A circuit breaker is an essential electrical safety device used to protect electrical circuits and appliances from damage caused by overcurrents or short circuits. It acts as a switch that automatically interrupts or breaks the flow of electricity in a circuit when it detects an abnormal current flow.

equipments.name: Voltage Regulator
equipments.description: A voltage regulator is an electrical device used to stabilize the output voltage of a power supply. It ensures that the voltage remains constant within a predetermined range, even when the input voltage or load conditions fluctuate. Voltage regulators are crucial in maintaining the proper functioning of sensitive electronic equipment and preventing damage caused by voltage variations.

equipments.name: Solar Panel
equipments.description: A solar panel, also known as a photovoltaic (PV) panel, is an electrical device that converts sunlight into direct current (DC) electricity. Solar panels are a key component of solar energy systems and are used to harness renewable solar energy for various applications, including powering homes, businesses, and remote installations. They play a crucial role in reducing reliance on traditional fossil fuels and mitigating greenhouse gas emissions.

equipments.name: Programmable Logic Controller (PLC)
equipments.description: A Programmable Logic Controller (PLC) is an industrial digital computer used to automate and control manufacturing processes, machinery, and other industrial applications. PLCs are programmable and can be easily customized to perform specific tasks through a graphical programming interface. They are widely used in factories and industries to improve efficiency, accuracy, and reliability in production processes.

equipments.name: Power Transformer
equipments.description: A power transformer is a vital electrical device used in power transmission and distribution systems to step up or step down voltage levels. It efficiently transfers electrical energy between different voltage levels while maintaining the power frequency. Power transformers play a crucial role in the efficient and reliable transfer of electrical power over long distances, reducing energy losses and ensuring a stable power supply to end consumers.

equipment.name: Power Distribution Unit
